<font color="#FF0000">GOODBYE!</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 16 11:48:55 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Fellows,<br><br>
It's been nice discussing issues, finding out about things, establishing positions and having them challenged, feeling out other people's perceptions of events, discussing areas of concern, enjoying camaraderie, and understanding just a bit more of the history we lived through.  <br><br>
But this last few weeks, the discussions have taken a turn toward the language, insults and jeering that led to my decision to leave the service.  This is not the lifestyle I like, and I do not have to participate.  I'll be checking in once in a while, but for this ex-PJ, enough is enough.  <br><br>
Goodbye.<br><br>
(By the way, you have probably succeeded in getting this site knocked off the school kids list of sites of historic importance.  It shows a certain lack of self-control.  Congratulations!)
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


